    "description": "Likely founded by Attalos II, Hellenopolis was initially populated by an amalgamation of citizens from several nearby Greek cities, and was located somewhere near the Mysia-Bithynia border.",
    "details": "<p>This site is different from <a class=\"external-link\" href=\"../511240\" target=\"_self\" title=\"\">https://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511240</a> as \"This Hellenopolis should be distinguished from Drepanon on the Astakene Gulf, which was renamed Helenopolis by Constantine the Great in honor of his mother (Amm. Marc. 26.8.1).\" (<a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/2533/pleiades/items/itemKey/PRP2TT93/\" target=\"_self\" title=\"\">Cohen, s.v. </a><span><em><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/2533/pleiades/items/itemKey/PRP2TT93/\" target=\"_self\" title=\"\">Hellenopolis</a></em>)</span></p>",
